<p><a name="Notes" id="Notes"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Trust_law&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="references-small">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Roy_Goode" title="Roy Goode">Roy Goode</a>, <i>Commercial Law</i> (2nd ed.)</li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> See for example <i><a href="/wiki/T_Choithram_International_SA_v_Pagarani" title="T Choithram International SA v Pagarani">T Choithram International SA and others v Pagarani and others</a></i> [2001] 2 All ER 492</li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2" title="">^</a></b> For example, in England, trusts over land must be evidenced in writing under s.56 of the Law of Property Act 1925</li>
<li id="cite_note-3"><b><a href="#cite_ref-3" title="">^</a></b> Kam Fan Sin, The Legal Nature of the Unit Trust, Clarendon Press, 1998.</li>
</ol>
</div>
