<li><a href="/wiki/Charles_Mitchell_(academic)" title="Charles Mitchell (academic)" class="mw-redirect">Charles Mitchell</a>, David Hayton and Paul Matthews, <i>Underhill and Hayton's Law Relating to Trusts and Trustees</i> (Butterworths, 2006) 17th edn (winner of the Society of Trusts and Estates Practitioners’ Book of the Year Award for 2007</li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFGaudiosi1988">Gaudiosi, Monica M. (April 1988), "The Influence of the Islamic Law of Waqf on the Development of the Trust in England: The Case of Merton College", <i><a href="/wiki/University_of_Pennsylvania_Law_Review" title="University of Pennsylvania Law Review">University of Pennsylvania Law Review</a></i> <b>136</b>&#160;(4): 1231-1261</cite></li>
<li><cite id="CITEREFHudson2003">Hudson, A. (2003), <i>Equity and Trusts</i> (3rd ed.), Cavendish Publishing, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1859417299" class="internal">ISBN 1-85941-729-9</a></cite></li>
